1. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the capacity region of a Gaussian relay-interference network. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on facilitating competing information flows over a wireless network. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper deals with network decomposition techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possibility as the paper deals with interference management techniques using structured lattice codes. 
5. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper proposes a new interference management scheme.
